    <stitle>CAB: 5000i AND 9000i CONVENTIONAL - REMOVE - INSTRUMENT PANEL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>INSTRUMENT PANEL</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1602125">Figure 25</hotlnk>
                for instrument panel locations of speedometer, tachometer, gauges and switches.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove Electrically Operated Gauges, Mechanical Air Gauges and Speedometer/Tachometer</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove electrically operated gauges, mechanical air gauges, speedometer and
                    tachometer, refer to
                    <emph type="bold">GROUP 08 - ELECTRICAL</emph>
                    in the
                    <emph type="bold">Master Service Manual</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>To remove face panel where the radio is located, the radio bezel (cover) will have to be
                        removed. To remove radio bezel, grab the bezel on each side of the radio, and carefully pull
                        bezel off the radio.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To access fuse panel or circuit breaker panel (optional) located behind glove box, open
                    glove box
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1602125">(Item 6, Figure 25)</hotlnk>. Reach behind glove box from top and pull
                    glove box stops inward to allow glove box to drop down out of the way. If more clearance is
                    required, pull glove box stops inward, which will allow glove box to drop down past second stop.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1602125" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg16/G1602125.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="368px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>Figure 25. Instrument Panel</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LEFT GAUGES AND LIGHTS CLUSTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TACHOMETER AND SPEEDOMETER CENTER GAUGE CLUSTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RIGHT GAUGES AND LIGHTS CLUSTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. WING PANEL (CONTAINS SWITCH PANEL, RADIO, HEATER/COOLING CONTROLS AND OPTIONAL SWITCHES
                        AND GAUGES)
                    </callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RADIO</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. GLOVE BOX (FUSE/CIRCUIT BREAKER (OPTIONAL) PANEL BEHIND)</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. TWO-POST TERMINAL POWER SOURCE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. CIGAR TYPE POWER SOURCE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. AIR SUSPENSION DUMP (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. AIR RECIRCULATION KNOB</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. CENTER CONVENIENCE CONSOLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. CIGAR LIGHTER</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. VERNIER THROTTLE (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. EATON TANDEM REAR AXLE OR TRACTION DIFFERENTIAL CONTROL (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. PUSH BUTTON STARTING OR AIR STARTER (OPTIONAL)</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. DIAGNOSTIC CONNECTION; ELECTRONIC ENGINES</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. KEY SWITCH</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
